title: UIW in celebratory mood after rallying past Northwestern State
text:

Image 1 of 1 Incarnate Word quarterback Trent Brittain shows how tight end Cole Wick waved his arms to show that he was open in the end zone for a touchdown pass during college football action against Nicholls State at Benson Stadium on Saturday, Sept. 19, 2015.
Photo: Billy Calzada, Staff / San Antonio Express-News Incarnate Word quarterback Trent Brittain shows how tight end Cole... UIW in celebratory mood after rallying past Northwestern State 1 / 1 Back to Gallery Larry Kennan threw open the locker room doors and walked right into a celebration, jubilant players throwing water and hugging each other.
His UIW team just won a midseason football game, beating Southland Conference foe Northwestern State 45-31 on Saturday at Benson Stadium.
